				"description": "## Register User\n\nThis endpoint is used to register a new user in the system. It accepts user information and creates a new account.\n\n### Request\n\n- **Method**: POST\n    \n- **URL**: `http://127.0.0.1:1234/api/v1/auth/register`\n    \n\n#### Request Body\n\nThe request body must be sent in JSON format. It should contain the necessary user details for registration. The expected structure of the request body is as follows:\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"username\": \"string\",\n  \"email\": \"string\",\n  \"password\": \"string\"\n}\n\n ```\n\n- `username`: The desired username for the new account.\n    \n- `email`: The email address of the user.\n    \n- `password`: The password for the account.\n    \n\n### Response\n\nUpon successful registration, the API will return a response indicating the success of the operation. The expected structure of the response is as follows:\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"message\": \"User registered successfully.\",\n  \"userId\": \"string\"\n}\n\n ```\n\n- `success`: A boolean indicating whether the registration was successful.\n    \n- `message`: A message detailing the result of the registration attempt.\n    \n- `userId`: The unique identifier assigned to the newly registered user.\n    \n\n### Notes\n\n- Ensure that all required fields are provided in the request body.\n    \n- The email must be unique and in a valid format."
			},
